#: ../../../howtos/collect_licenses.rst:4
msgid "How to collect licenses of dependencies"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../howtos/collect_licenses.rst:6
msgid ""
"With the ``imports`` feature it is possible to collect the License files "
"from all packages in the dependency graph. Please note that the licenses are "
"artifacts that must exist in the binary packages to be collected, as "
"different binary packages might have different licenses. E.g., A package "
"creator might provide a different license for static or shared linkage with "
"different \"License\" files if they want to."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../howtos/collect_licenses.rst:10
msgid ""
"Also, we will assume the convention that the package authors will provide a "
"\"License\" (case not important) file at the root of their packages."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../howtos/collect_licenses.rst:13
msgid "In *conanfile.txt* we would use the following syntax:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../howtos/collect_licenses.rst:15
msgid ""
"[imports]\n"
"., license* -> ./licenses @ folder=True, ignore_case=True"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../howtos/collect_licenses.rst:20
msgid "And in *conanfile.py* we will use the ``imports()`` method:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../howtos/collect_licenses.rst:22
msgid ""
"def imports(self):\n"
"     self.copy(\"license*\", dst=\"licenses\", folder=True, ignore_case=True)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../howtos/collect_licenses.rst:27
msgid ""
"In both cases, after :command:`conan install`, it will store all the found "
"License files inside the local **licenses** folder, which will contain one "
"subfolder per dependency with the license file inside."
msgstr ""
